---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SubscribeBox from '../components/SubscribeBox.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About the Car — projekt36"
  description="The story of a 1994 BMW E36 316i Sedan — where it came from, what it is, and what it's becoming. A complete transformation documented from first fault code to final drive."
>

<div class="about-page">

  <!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
  <div class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-tag">PROJEKT36 · THE CAR</div>
    <h1 class="about-title">One E36.<br><em>One transformation.</em></h1>
    <p class="about-lead">
      A 1994 BMW E36 316i Sedan — bought tired, with 230,000 kilometres on the clock
      and a list of faults longer than the service history. Not a pristine shell. Not a
      competition car. A real car, with real problems, being fixed the right way.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ IMAGE SLOT 1 — full-width car photo ═══ -->
  <!-- SUGGESTED IMAGE: wide exterior shot of the car as-found / arrival condition -->
  <!-- dimensions: 1200×600px or wider, showing the car from the front-three-quarter -->
  <div class="about-img-slot about-img-wide">
    <div class="img-placeholder">
      <span class="img-placeholder-label">[ Photo — Car as found, exterior, front ¾ ]</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE CAR ═══ -->
  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-section-tag">The machine</div>
    <h2 class="about-h2">What it is</h2>
    <p>
      E36 316i Sedan, built in 1994. Munich steel, four-cylinder M43B16 engine producing
      102 hp, five-speed manual gearbox, rear-wheel drive. Alpine White over Anthracite cloth.
      The E36 was BMW's bread-and-butter car of the nineties — not exotic, but engineered
      with the same fundamentals as the M3 that shared its platform.
    </p>
    <p>
      The 316i was the entry-level variant. That is precisely the point. The bones are
      identical to the six-cylinder cars — same suspension geometry, same subframe, same
      body shell. The M43 is a placeholder. Everything else is the foundation.
    </p>

    <!-- SUGGESTED IMAGE: engine bay photo showing the M43 in situ, before any work -->
    <!-- dimensions: 900×600px, well-lit engine bay shot -->
    <div class="about-img-slot">
      <div class="img-placeholder">
        <span class="img-placeholder-label">[ Photo — Original M43 engine bay ]</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-spec-table">
      <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Model</span><span class="spec-val">BMW 316i Sedan (E36)</span></div>
      <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Year</span><span class="spec-val">1994</span></div>
      <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Engine</span><span class="spec-val">M43B16 · 1,596 cc · 102 hp</span></div>
      <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Gearbox</span><span class="spec-val">Getrag 5-speed manual</span></div>
      <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Colour</span><span class="spec-val">Alpine White (300)</span></div>
      <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Odometer</span><span class="spec-val">230,000+ km at acquisition</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE CONDITION ═══ -->
  <div class="about-section about-section-alt">
    <div class="about-section-tag">Starting point</div>
    <h2 class="about-h2">Where it came from</h2>
    <p>
      The car arrived with the kind of history common to high-mileage E36s: cooling system
      leaks deferred too long, rust starting in the sills and rear arches, electrical faults
      never traced to root cause, and a service record that stopped being stamped around
      150,000 kilometres. Driveable. Far from right.
    </p>
    <p>
      The structural condition was assessed first. Sill rust was surface-level on one side,
      deeper on the other. The rear arch lips had bubbled but not perforated. The floor and
      inner sills were clean. A car worth saving — but only if done properly.
    </p>

    <!-- SUGGESTED IMAGE: pair of photos — rust detail on sill / rear arch close-up -->
    <!-- dimensions: two images side by side, each ~600×400px -->
    <div class="about-img-slot about-img-pair">
      <div class="img-placeholder">
        <span class="img-placeholder-label">[ Photo — Sill rust detail ]</span>
      </div>
      <div class="img-placeholder">
        <span class="img-placeholder-label">[ Photo — Rear arch bubbling ]</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE PLAN ═══ -->
  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-section-tag">The transformation</div>
    <h2 class="about-h2">What it's becoming</h2>
    <p>
      The goal is a complete transformation across eleven chapters — not a show car,
      not a track car, but a genuinely sorted driver's machine built to last another
      200,000 kilometres. Every system addressed, nothing bodged.
    </p>

    <div class="about-transform-grid">
      <div class="transform-col transform-now">
        <div class="transform-label">Now</div>
        <ul>
          <li>M43B16 · 102 hp · 4-cylinder</li>
          <li>Stock suspension · worn bushings</li>
          <li>Grey cloth interior · no insulation</li>
          <li>Rust in sills and arches</li>
          <li>Manual windows · no climate control</li>
          <li>Steel 15" wheels</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="transform-col transform-become">
        <div class="transform-label">Becoming</div>
        <ul>
          <li>M50B25 NV · 189 hp · inline-6</li>
          <li>Air suspension · full geometry reset</li>
          <li>Black leather · full sound deadening</li>
          <li>Rust-free · fresh paint + PPF</li>
          <li>Climate control retrofit</li>
          <li>Custom 3-piece wheels</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SUGGESTED IMAGE: mood/inspiration photo — a clean E36 Sedan showing the target aesthetic -->
    <!-- dimensions: 900×500px, ideally a side-on or rear ¾ shot of a similar-spec finished car -->
    <div class="about-img-slot">
      <div class="img-placeholder">
        <span class="img-placeholder-label">[ Photo — Target aesthetic reference or inspiration ]</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ WHY DOCUMENTED ═══ -->
  <div class="about-section about-section-alt">
    <div class="about-section-tag">Why this site exists</div>
    <h2 class="about-h2">The documentation</h2>
    <p>
      The E36 is a well-understood car — thirty years of ownership, a deep parts network,
      and plenty of forum threads. What it lacks is documentation that is structured,
      accurate, and honest about the failures as much as the successes.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every decision on this car is written down: what was done, why, what it cost, what
      went wrong, and what was learned. The guides come from that work directly — not copied
      from forums, not speculative, but tested on this specific car and cross-referenced
      against BMW's own ETM and repair documentation.
    </p>
    <p>
      The tools section exists because the same calculations kept coming up — wheel fitment,
      offset, tire diameter, swap compatibility — and a spreadsheet gets old quickly.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ ABOUT THE PERSON ═══ -->
  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-section-tag">Behind the build</div>
    <h2 class="about-h2">Who's doing this</h2>

    <!-- SUGGESTED IMAGE: portrait or workshop photo — informal, working on the car -->
    <!-- dimensions: 320×320px square, or 400×300px, positioned float-right on desktop -->
    <div class="about-img-slot about-img-person">
      <div class="img-placeholder">
        <span class="img-placeholder-label">[ Photo — Portrait or workshop shot ]</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      <!-- FILL IN: your name or handle, where you're based, a line about background -->
      I'm [your name], based in [location]. [One sentence about your background — what you do,
      how long you've been into cars, or how you ended up with an E36.]
    </p>
    <p>
      <!-- FILL IN: how you got into the E36 specifically, what drew you to this project -->
      [A paragraph about why this specific car — why the E36, why a 316i as the starting point,
      what the project means to you beyond just having a working car at the end of it.]
    </p>
    <p>
      <!-- FILL IN: your approach, skills, what you do yourself vs. outsource -->
      [A paragraph about how you work — what you do yourself, what you outsource, your
      philosophy on how the build should be done. Readers find this context useful when
      deciding how much to trust the guides.]
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ SUBSCRIBE ═══ -->
  <SubscribeBox />

  <!-- ═══ FOOTER NOTE ═══ -->
  <div class="about-footer-note">
    <span class="about-footer-mono">// build in progress · documentation updated as work completes</span>
    <a href="/build" class="btn-primary">Follow the build →</a>
  </div>

</div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .about-hero {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .about-hero-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .about-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .about-lead {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-mid);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .about-section {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .about-section-alt {
    background: var(--bg2);
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    margin: 0 -2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .about-section-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .about-h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.8rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .about-section p,
  .about-section-alt p {
    color: var(--text-mid);
    line-height: 1.85;
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  /* Image placeholders */
  .about-img-slot {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  .about-img-wide {
    margin: 0 0 3rem;
  }
  .about-img-pair {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .about-img-pair { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .img-placeholder {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px dashed var(--border-mid);
    aspect-ratio: 3/2;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 1rem;
  }
  .about-img-wide .img-placeholder { aspect-ratio: 21/9; }
  .img-placeholder-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Spec table */
  .about-spec-table {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin: 1.75rem 0;
  }
  .spec-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .spec-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .spec-key {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 0.65rem 1rem;
    background: var(--bg2);
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .spec-val {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--text-mid);
    padding: 0.65rem 1rem;
  }

  /* Transformation grid */
  .about-transform-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin: 1.75rem 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .about-transform-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .transform-col {
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .transform-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .transform-now  .transform-label { color: var(--text-dim); }
  .transform-become .transform-label { color: var(--accent); }
  .transform-col ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .transform-col li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    padding: 0.45rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .transform-col li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .transform-now     li { color: var(--text-dim); }
  .transform-become  li { color: var(--text-mid); }

  /* Footer note */
  .about-footer-note {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .about-footer-mono {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .about-img-person {
    float: right;
    width: 220px;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 2rem;
  }
  .about-img-person .img-placeholder { aspect-ratio: 4/3; }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .about-section-alt { margin: 0 -1.5rem; padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem; }
    .about-img-person { float: none; width: 100%; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }
  }
</style>
